						<div class="postbody">It sounds like, as long as you're wedded to using the EverdriveGB, you're probably restricted to having to make a token mapper hack to be compatible with the MBC1 registers.<br /><br />That said, I'm pretty certain pretending to use an MBC1 is nowhere near as big of an endeavor as you're fearing it is. I'm pretty certain it's just a matter of inserting the fifteen bytes I suggested earlier and hoping that the Everdrive GB's SRAM handler is robust to when the game turns off.</div>

